    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Preprocessing\n",
        "\n",
        "- Here, I normalize the stock prices using MinMaxScaler and convert the data into sequences.  \n",
        "- I am using a time step of 120, which means the model looks at the past 120 days to predict the next value."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4haeHTyP8xn3"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "features = df[['Close', 'MA10', 'MA50', 'Returns']]\n",
        "\n",
        "scaler = MinMaxScaler()\n",
        "scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(features)\n",
        "\n",
        "time_step = 120\n",
        "\n",
        "def create_sequences(data, time_step):\n",
        "    X, y = [], []\n",
        "    for i in range(time_step, len(data)):\n",
        "        X.append(data[i-time_step:i])\n",
        "        y.append(data[i, 0])  # predict Close price\n",
        "    return np.array(X), np.array(y)\n",
        "\n",
        "X, y = create_sequences(scaled_data, time_step)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_d_oG5Zj8coK"
      },
      "execution_count": 52,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Train-Test-Split"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "p7yH2ClQ9ACE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "split = int(0.8 * len(X))\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train, X_test = X[:split], X[split:]\n",
        "y_train, y_test = y[:split], y[split:]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jSotQuoZ815W"
      },
      "execution_count": 53,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### LSTM Model\n",
        "\n",
        "I am using a stacked LSTM model to learn patterns from time-series data and predict future stock prices."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "crnlUINh9LAr"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "early_stopping_callback = callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dV7prFqV99hz"
      },
      "execution_count": 21,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.LSTM(64, return_sequences=True, input_shape=(X.shape[1], X.shape[2])),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.LSTM(64),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1)\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')\n",
        "\n",
        "history = model.fit(\n",
        "    X_train, y_train,\n",
        "    epochs=20,\n",
        "    batch_size=32,\n",
        "    validation_data=(X_test, y_test)\n",
        ")"
      ],
